cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the logical part of psi-calculi and their expressive power in accommodating a wide range of logics. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as psi-calculi are a framework for nominal calculi, which are used to model programming languages. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper deals with event-based models of concurrency, which can be seen as a type of data structure. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possible category as the paper deals with encoding event-based models into psi-calculi, which can be seen as a software engineering task. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a less likely category, but still possible as psi-calculi are a type of process algebra, which is a formal language for describing concurrent systems.
